('4.5.0.0', 'Manitowoc Tool and Manufacturing WIP Application\nVersion: 4.5.0.0\nRelease Date: 1/5/2025\n\nPatch Notes:\n\n1/6/2025 Hotfix - You can no longer have more than 1 instance of the application open at once.\n\nNew Feature - Change Log (You are currently reading it)\n\nBug Fixes and code rework of Personal History.\n\nNew Bug Reporting System - In the Event of an error the application will now upload the error details to the WIP server so I can more easily pinpoint problems with the application.  No need to tell me about errors anymore! Well still do, but I can catch them as well.\n\nTransfer Tab Quantity - You can now input a quantity into the Transfer Tab, doing so will split the quantity between the old location and the location you are moving it to.\n\nNo more having to restart after Adding or Removing New Part Numbers, Locations, Users, exc...\n\nWhen exiting the Multiple entries screen, via the Inventory Tab the main window will now reset like it should.\n\nRenamed the 3 tabs to Inventory, Removal and Transfer Tabs those names just seem to make more sense.\n\nUsed AI to look over all methods in the application and had it rework a lot of the code for better performance.', '2025-08-10', 'SYSTEM', 'Manitowoc Tool and Manufacturing WIP Application\nVersion: 4.5.0.0\nRelease Date: 1/5/2025\n\nPatch Notes:\n\n1/6/2025 Hotfix - You can no longer have more than 1 instance of the application open at once.\n\nNew Feature - Change Log (You are currently reading it)\n\nBug Fixes and code rework of Personal History.\n\nNew Bug Reporting System - In the Event of an error the application will now upload the error details to the WIP server so I can more easily pinpoint problems with the application.  No need to tell me about errors anymore! Well still do, but I can catch them as well.\n\nTransfer Tab Quantity - You can now input a quantity into the Transfer Tab, doing so will split the quantity between the old location and the location you are moving it to.\n\nNo more having to restart after Adding or Removing New Part Numbers, Locations, Users, exc...\n\nWhen exiting the Multiple entries screen, via the Inventory Tab the main window will now reset like it should.\n\nRenamed the 3 tabs to Inventory, Removal and Transfer Tabs those names just seem to make more sense.\n\nUsed AI to look over all methods in the application and had it rework a lot of the code for better performance.', '2025-08-10 18:40:45', '2025-08-10 18:40:45'),
('4.5.0.1', 'Manitowoc Tool and Manufacturing WIP Application\r\nVersion: 4.5.0.1\r\nRelease Date: 1/6/2025\r\n\r\nPatch Notes:\r\n\r\n1/6/2025 Hotfix - You can no longer have more than 1 instance of the application open at once.', '2025-08-10', 'SYSTEM', 'Manitowoc Tool and Manufacturing WIP Application\r\nVersion: 4.5.0.1\r\nRelease Date: 1/6/2025\r\n\r\nPatch Notes:\r\n\r\n1/6/2025 Hotfix - You can no longer have more than 1 instance of the application open at once.', '2025-08-10 18:40:45', '2025-08-10 18:40:45'),
('4.5.0.2', '{\\rtf1\\ansi\\ansicpg1252\\deff0\\nouicompat\\deflang1033{\\fonttbl{\\f0\\fnil\\fcharset0 Segoe UI;}{\\f1\\fnil\\fcharset2 Symbol;}}\r\n{\\colortbl ;\\red30\\green30\\blue30;}\r\n{\\*\\generator Riched20 10.0.19041}\\viewkind4\\uc1 \r\n\\pard\\cf1\\b\\f0\\fs20 Date:\\b0  01/12/2025\\line\\b Version:\\b0  4.5.0.2\\par\r\n\\par\r\n\\b New Feature: Note Editor (Used for Assembly to add Work Order #s to exsisting Transactions)\\b0\\par\r\nThis method allows users to edit notes for selected items in the Remove tab. It helps users view and update notes related to different parts and operations.\\par\r\n\\par\r\n\\b How to Use (Only usable in the Removal Tab, not the Transaction Tab):\\b0\\par\r\n\r\n\\pard \r\n{\\pntext\\f0 1.\\tab}{\\*\\pn\\pnlvlbody\\pnf0\\pnindent0\\pnstart1\\pndec{\\pntxta.}}\r\n\\fi-360\\li720\\b Select Items:\\b0  Click on the items in the list that you want to edit. You can select multiple items by holding down the Ctrl key while clicking.\\par\r\n{\\pntext\\f0 2.\\tab}\\b Click Edit:\\b0  Click the \"Edit\" button to open the edit window.\\par\r\n{\\pntext\\f0 3.\\tab}\\b Edit Notes:\\b0  In the edit window, you can change the notes for the selected items.\\par\r\n{\\pntext\\f0 4.\\tab}\\b Editing Notes:\\b0  You can edit the notes in the text box. Click the save button to save your changes. If there are more notes, it will show the next one.\\par\r\n{\\pntext\\f0 5.\\tab}\\b Skipping Notes:\\b0  Click the skip button to move to the next note without saving any changes.\\par\r\n{\\pntext\\f0 6.\\tab}\\b Exiting:\\b0  When you are done, click the save button when it says \"Exit\" to close the form.\\par\r\n\r\n\\pard\\b\\par\r\nMinor Changes:\\b0\\par\r\n\r\n\\pard{\\pntext\\f1\\\'B7\\tab}{\\*\\pn\\pnlvlblt\\pnf1\\pnindent0{\\pntxtb\\\'B7}}\\fi-360\\li720 The Change Log window will now only show up when the application starts unless the checkbox is below is checked.\\b\\par\r\n{\\pntext\\f1\\\'B7\\tab}\\b0 \"Don\'t show until next pat